RCA to Low CSAT ‚Äì Agentic AI Application Summary In a professional services company, low Customer Satisfaction (CSAT) scores can negatively impact client retention and brand reputation. Root Cause Analysis (RCA) is a critical business process used to identify the underlying reasons for declining CSAT. Agentic AI can optimize this process by autonomously analyzing large volumes of customer feedback and operational data from clients such as a Global Bank or Retail Giant. The AI agent perceives customer sentiment by processing survey responses, service tickets, and feedback comments. Using reasoning capabilities, it identifies patterns and correlations between low CSAT scores and factors such as delayed service delivery, communication gaps, or recurring technical issues. Through planning, the AI recommends corrective actions, prioritizes high-impact issues, and continuously tracks improvements after changes are implemented. The AI agent requires anonymized customer feedback data, service performance metrics, and resolution timelines. The key benefits include faster identification of root causes, reduced manual effort, improved accuracy, and proactive decision-making. By leveraging Agentic AI, organizations can move from reactive problem-solving to continuous service improvement, ultimately leading to higher customer satisfaction and stronger client relationships.


